Welcome to Creamer Media’s Resources Watch, a weekly video round-up of the events and people making and shaping the news in the mining industry. This week: Coal miner Exxaro driving rigorous renewable energy strategy Menar doing due diligence on thermal coal assets being offloaded And, Coronavirus likely to cause drastic price falls South Africa’s electricity generation crisis has created major opportunities for companies, businesses and individuals to start generating their own power. Exxaro CEO Mxolisi Mgojo:  Private investment and management company Menar is doing due diligence on thermal coal assets that have been placed on the market by companies wishing to offload them out of their portfolios.  Menar MD Vuslat Bayoǧlu:  The reduction in the consumption of mined products that the coronavirus was causing would likely result in a drastic fall in prices.  Menar MD Vuslat Bayoğlu:  For mining news as it breaks, stay logged onto Mining Weekly.com and register for our free daily newsletter.